metadata.name: Volo di porpora
metadata.description: The color purple, with its unique combination of blue and red, represents the integration of the rational and irrational, the masculine and feminine. It symbolizes the transcendence of the base, material world and the ascent towards the spiritual realm. It is not just a mere visual sensation, but a representation of the highest human aspirations. The purple is a reminder of what we are capable of becoming, of the highest and most noble aspects of our existence. It serves as a symbol of the quest for wisdom, the cultivation of the soul and the attainment of the sacred. The purple is not just a color, it is an invitation to greatness.
